      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Description</h2>
        <p>
          Dust, fibers, and static contamination on polarizer surfaces are a leading cause of defects
          in display panel production — affecting lamination yield, inspection accuracy, and finished
          product appearance. The DGSDK Polarizer Precision Cleaning Machine is built to address this
          directly, providing automatic surface cleaning before critical downstream processes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Designed for polarizer films and optical sheet materials, the machine integrates controlled
          cleaning mechanics and static elimination to remove sub-micron particles without damaging
          sensitive film surfaces. It fits into existing production lines before lamination,
          AOI inspection, or packaging stages.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Product Features</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>All-new magnetic levitation drive design — smooth, stable operation</li>
          <li>Thin cleaning layer — does not deform or crease polarizer film materials</li>
          <li>Special precision adhesive rollers — superior cleaning results, improves polarizer yield</li>
          <li>Quick-change roller structure for fast maintenance</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="detail-block">
        <h2>Technical Advantages</h2>
        <div class="advantage-grid">
          <div class="advantage-card blue">
            <h3>Magnetic Levitation</h3>
            <p>Frictionless drive ensures stable, vibration-free transport of sensitive polarizer films.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card yellow">
            <h3>Higher Yield</h3>
            <p>Precision adhesive rollers remove particles and static to reduce polarizer production defects.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="advantage-card green">
            <h3>Quick-Change</h3>
            <p>Fast roller replacement structure minimizes downtime in display manufacturing lines.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

